rom Old French <i>Lucie</i>, the vernacular form of   Lucia .  It is sometimes assumed that <i>Lucy</i> is a pet form of   Lucinda  , but there is no etymological justification for this assumption. It was in fairly widespread use in the Middle Ages, and increased greatly in popularity in the 18th century and again in the 1990s. In Ireland it serves as an Anglicized form of Irish Luíseach ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lucy Mayfield was born in 1311, in Thornhill, West Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Mayfield, was 26 and her mother, Mrs. John Mayfield, was 22. She married Thomas Drakes in 1334, in Huddersfield, West Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 5 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1311–":"1311–Surnud","1311–Female":"1311–Surnud","1307–Male":"1307–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1337–1389":"1337–1389","1339–Male":"1339–Surnud","1341–Male":"1341–Surnud","1343–Male":"1343–Surnud","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","1289–Female":"1289–Surnud","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1335":"umbes 1335","Abt 1345":"umbes 1345","Abt 1339":"umbes 1339","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1334":"1334","1345":"1345","1389":"1389","1311":"1311","Abt 1343":"umbes 1343","1289":"1289","1343":"1343","Abt 1341":"umbes 1341","1307":"1307","1339":"1339","Thornhill, Dewsbury, West Yorkshire, England":"Thornhill, West Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woodsome Hall, Huddersfield, West Yorkshire, England":"Huddersfield, West Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1311–":"1311–Kuollut","1311–Female":"1311–Kuollut","1307–Male":"1307–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1337–1389":"1337–1389","1339–Male":"1339–Kuollut","1341–Male":"1341–Kuollut","1343–Male":"1343–Kuollut","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","1289–Female":"1289–Kuollut","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1335":"noin 1335","Abt 1345":"noin 1345","Abt 1339":"noi